{"cursor":"15013","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Analog' (or 'analogue') 'recording' (Greek, ana is \"according to\" and logos\n\"relationship\") is a technique used for the recording of analog signals which\namong many possibilities include audio frequency, analog audio and analog video\ninformation for later playback.\n\nAnalog recording methods store signals as a continual wave in or on the\nmedia. The wave might be stored as a physical texture on a phonograph record,\nor a fluctuation in the field strength of a magnetic recording. This is\ndifferent from digital recording of which among many possibilities include\ndigital audio and digital video, which digital signals are represented as\ndata or discrete numbers.\n","linknr":456,"url":"Analogue_recording","recorded":1362580094,"links":26,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Film and video technology","Film and video terminology","Media technology","Recording","Television terminology","Video storage"],"headings":["The Phonograph","The Gramophone","The Telegraphone","The Magnetophon","A.C. Bias","The Digital Age","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Edison_and_phonograph_edit1.jpg/220px-Edison_and_phonograph_edit1.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/BerlinerDisc1897.jpg/220px-BerlinerDisc1897.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/US_Patent_661%2C619_-_Magnetic_recorder.jpg/220px-US_Patent_661%2C619_-_Magnetic_recorder.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3f/Valdemar-poulsen-c1898.jpg/220px-Valdemar-poulsen-c1898.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Ton_S.b%2C_ta